    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ddd26d89_49c621a6",
        "filename": "util/win/nt_internals.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-12T15:58:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not a good place for this function.\n\nnt_internals.{h,cc} are for NT internals that the SDK does not expose in headers, but where we say “we mostly know what we’re doing, we’re gonna use these anyway.” It’s not a good home for arbitrary utilities around public \u003cwinnt.h\u003e interfaces, because those don’t really fit the model of the “internals” that we’ve grouped together here.\n\nA new header dedicated to this function would be fine if it doesn’t fit anywhere. Don’t forget to provide //! Doxygen documentation. (Doxygen wasn’t necessary in nt_internals.h because these functions all just wrap hidden NT functions, they’re not our own original work.)",
      "revId": "95e2f72191ebcb5f1ff0ca33d4c81487d4a1ea4a",
